    "datePublished": "2021-06-01",
    "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com/disc-centrifuge-cannot-reach-operating-speed/",
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why won't my disc centrifuge reach full operating speed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The most common causes are a worn or slipping friction clutch that cannot transfer enough torque, motor issues (under-voltage, single-phasing, or undersized motor), worn or damaged bowl bearings causing excessive drag, an imbalanced or damaged bowl assembly, or excessive feed flow during startup that overloads the drive." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does a friction clutch affect centrifuge startup speed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The friction clutch couples the motor to the bowl spindle during startup. A slipping or worn clutch cannot transfer enough torque to accelerate the heavy bowl to rated RPM. If startup takes longer than 15 minutes or the bowl never reaches rated speed, inspect and replace the clutch shoes." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What should I check if my centrifuge speed is lower than rated RPM?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Check: (1) brake is disengaged, (2) clutch condition and spring tension, (3) supply voltage and motor current draw, (4) bowl bearing temperature and noise, (5) bowl assembly balance, and (6) whether the bowl was recently disassembled and may have been reassembled incorrectly." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can reverse rotation prevent a centrifuge from reaching speed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. A phase reversal of the electric supply causes reverse rotation. The friction clutch design only allows torque transmission in the correct direction, so the bowl cannot reach operating speed. Reverse rotation also unlocks threaded bowl parts (left-hand thread), which can cause catastrophic damage. Always verify motor rotation direction after any electrical work." }
      }
    ]
  }
];

